Consumers Power Co is raising 250 mlndlrs through a two-tranche offering of first mortgage bonds,said lead manager Morgan Stanley and Co Inc.    A 150 mln dlr offering due 1992 was given a nine pct couponand par pricing to yield 112.5 basis points over comparableTreasuries. This tranche is non-callable for life.    A companion 100 mln dlr issue maturing in 1997 was assigneda 9-5/8 pct coupon and priced at 98.50 to yield 9.703 pct, or143 basis points over Treasuries. These bonds are non-callablefor five years.    The debt is rated Baa-3 by Moody's, BBB-minus by S and P. Reuter&#3;